{"id":48416,"global_id":"Z2lkOi8vaGFja2Vyb25lL1JlcG9ydC80ODQxNg==","url":"https://hackerone.com/reports/48416","title":"Restrict any user from logging into his account.","state":"Closed","substate":"resolved","readable_substate":"Resolved","created_at":"2015-02-20T22:39:05.924Z","submitted_at":"2015-02-20T22:39:05.924Z","is_member_of_team?":false,"reporter":{"disabled":false,"username":"siddiki","url":"/siddiki","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/502/cf522f55c77430ca80c9ff947d022eb7e3d79350_original.png/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c"},"is_me?":false,"cleared":true,"hackerone_triager":false,"hacker_mediation":false},"team":{"id":13,"url":"https://hackerone.com/security","handle":"security","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/013/fa942b9b1cbf4faf37482bf68458e1195aab9c02_original.png/43e4513b9104ea0d68c9c096cea374ba8440dde3e027af5465c8771e8839a67c","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/013/fa942b9b1cbf4faf37482bf68458e1195aab9c02_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"permissions":[],"submission_state":"open","default_currency":"usd","awards_miles":false,"offers_bounties":true,"state":"public_mode","only_cleared_hackers":false,"pentest_feature_enabled?":false,"profile":{"name":"HackerOne","twitter_handle":"Hacker0x01","website":"https://hackerone.com","about":"Vulnerability disclosure should be safe, transparent, and rewarding."}},"has_bounty?":false,"in_validation?":false,"rejected_anc_report_that_can_be_sent_back_to_anc_triagers?":false,"can_view_team":true,"can_view_report":true,"is_external_bug":false,"is_published":false,"is_participant":false,"has_collaborators":false,"stage":4,"public":true,"visibility":"full","cve_ids":[],"singular_disclosure_disabled":false,"disclosed_at":"2015-03-24T00:56:05.924Z","bug_reporter_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2015-03-24T00:53:06.646Z","team_member_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2015-03-24T00:56:05.032Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hackerone's destroys user sessions automatically after signing out,changing password etc.So Old sessions are seems to be worthless for any attacker.But I found something,by exploiting this you can restrict any hackerone user to logging into his account.\r\n\r\n**Pre-Requisition**\r\nI just need one of his old sessions.\r\n\r\n**steps to reproduce**\r\n1. Login to hackerone.\r\n2. Capture any request.\r\n3. Send it to burp intruder.\r\n4. Logout from hackerone.\r\n5. Now start intruding that captured request,which is carrying the old destroyed session.\r\n6. Try log in from other device.\r\n7. Every time burp intruder sends a request,the present logged in account will be logged out automatically.\r\nSo if you keep continue intruding,that user will never be able to login to his own ID.","weakness":{"id":27,"name":"Improper Authentication - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2015-04-23T00:53:07.535Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-204214297.96698174,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":2,"voters":["jolansaluria","dyabla"],"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":336609,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNeedsMoreInfo","message":"But what are the security implications of this, other than being an annoyance to yourself? Because you are only able to capture requests of your own account. So if you would script something that logs yourself in automatically, you would only annoy yourself.\n\nYour prerequisite seems highly unobtainable. If you would be able to gain access to another user's account through hacking our platform, that report would be much more valuable to us.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-02-21T07:58:01.319Z","updated_at":"2015-02-21T07:58:31.521Z","actor":{"username":"jens","cleared":false,"url":"/jens","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/053/9c23f98571002dd0db70919126ae92746a6af99a_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":336616,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNew","message":"I saw hackerone accepted many reports related to user's session.Most of them were regarding,session not being destroyed after a password change,email change etc.So,what was the point on those case?The same way attacker would get hold on to victims session on those report,the same way attacker can obtain victim's old session.And once he got it ,he can refrain the victim user from logging into his own account.\nThe main issue is same here,old session is not completely destroyed.It can still be used to do some action.As I explained,it can be used to log out that particular user.\n**Referring to other report can never be a very good principle,I know it**.But you left me with no other option here.\n\nRef:\n1. https://hackerone.com/reports/17383\n2. https://hackerone.com/reports/15785\n3. https://hackerone.com/reports/288\n4. https://hackerone.com/reports/284\nIn all the above report,reporter needed to have access to one old session.So the pre-requisition  doesnt seem so strange.\nI hope I was able to clarify the matter.\n\nThanks","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-02-21T08:31:05.989Z","updated_at":"2015-02-21T08:31:05.989Z","actor":{"username":"siddiki","cleared":true,"url":"/siddiki","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/502/cf522f55c77430ca80c9ff947d022eb7e3d79350_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":337386,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugNotApplicable","message":"This just doesn't make sense to me. I still think your prerequisite is very hard to obtain. If this were a report where you'd explain how to obtain such a session by exploiting a vulnerability I wouldn't close this as Not Applicable, but I'm not seeing any security vulnerability. Destroying the session after logging out seems like a very good security measure to me. The last thing I would do as a hacker is annoy someone by destroying the victim's session â€“ there are much worse thing someone could do\n\nI'm afraid I have to close this as N/A. Keep hacking!","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-02-23T08:03:38.792Z","updated_at":"2015-02-23T08:03:38.792Z","actor":{"username":"jens","cleared":false,"url":"/jens","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/053/9c23f98571002dd0db70919126ae92746a6af99a_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":339121,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugReopened","message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-02-24T14:31:36.053Z","updated_at":"2015-02-24T14:31:36.053Z","actor":{"username":"wvdv","cleared":false,"url":"/wvdv","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/001/221/7503cfe93236733876c422fb69d8a9a81824802c_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hacke